    "title_zh": "条件概率与韦恩图",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "**Conditional probability** is the probability of an event occurring given that another event has already occurred. It is written as $P(A|B)$, which means 'the probability of A given B'.\n\n**The Formula** for conditional probability is: $P(A|B) = \\frac{P(A \\cap B)}{P(B)}$. This is often used with Venn diagrams by restricting the sample space to only circle B.\n\n**Venn Diagrams** help visualize overlapping sets. The intersection ($A \\cap B$) represents both events happening. The union ($A \\cup B$) represents at least one event happening. The complement ($A'$) represents the event not happening.",
      "zh": "**条件概率** (Conditional probability) 是指在已知另一个事件已发生的情况下，某个事件发生的概率。记作 $P(A|B)$，意思是“在 B 发生的条件下 A 发生的概率”。\n\n**公式** 为：$P(A|B) = \\frac{P(A \\cap B)}{P(B)}$。在韦恩图中，这通常意味着将样本空间限制在圆圈 B 内。\n\n**韦恩图** (Venn Diagrams) 有助于可视化重叠的集合。交集 ($A \\cap B$) 代表两个事件同时发生。并集 ($A \\cup B$) 代表至少有一个事件发生。补集 ($A'$) 代表事件不发生。"
    },
